```
$ tessera --help
Tessera FAIR data-product CLI

Usage: tessera <COMMAND>

Commands:
  inspect[..]Print a human summary of a `.tsra`'s manifest (id, product, blocks, hashes)
  verify[..]Open + fully verify a `.tsra` (magic, manifest seal, every block digest). Exit 0 if valid
  unpack[..]Explode a `.tsra` into a directory (`manifest.json` + `blocks/<name>`)
  pack[..]Pack an exploded directory (`manifest.json` + `blocks/`) into a sealed `.tsra`
  schema[..]Validate a `.tsra`'s manifest against its declared product schema (required fields/blocks)
  ingest[..]Ingest a vendor acquisition file into a sealed `.tsra` product (normalise at the door)
  export[..]Emit a FAIR discovery record for a `.tsra` (prints JSON to stdout)
  sign[..]Sign a sealed `.tsra` → writes a `<file>.sig.json` sidecar (ed25519 over `manifest_hash`)
  verify-sig[..]Verify a sealed `.tsra` against its `<file>.sig.json` sidecar + a trusted public key. Exit 0 if valid
  help[..]Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version

```
